  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't recall exactly which day it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He came back and join us, yes, already when we returned back to our old home in Sofia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After that, the Russians came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many of the Bulgarian partisan arrived back to the city, those who are people, basically young people, that used to fight Germans in an illegal way, hiding in the mountains, in the forests.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So they, first of all, they came to the city.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was actually very big emotions and big agitation between the population.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They, first of all, they [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] succeed to catch several of the fascist [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] officials, high officials, in the city.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And organized so-called-- so-called popular tribunals, in which some of them were executed, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] or shooted, or hanged even.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The prisons were freed of all these political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then I think what was happening, again is one of those mystical form of communication, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "How-- when the Jewish people start to communicated and know where they are supposed to go, and which train they are supposed to take.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they started-- I remember that my mother before that even we arrived to our home, she met with some of other cousins of ours.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] with the meager clothings that they had were-- I think that there were not too many problems of furniture and things like that; [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] start to open new page of the life of Jewish people, not for very long, however.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We arrive back to our home in order to see the ruins of our home, the home in which I was born.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
